-- Renault to Almost Double Share of Sales in Brazilian Market, Folha Reports
-- B y   T e l m a   M a r o t t o
-- 2010-10-03T15:26:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/renault-to-almost-double-share-of-sales-in-brazilian-market-folha-reports.html
Renault SA  plans to almost double its
share of car sales in Brazil in the next three years through
investments and by introducing new vehicles, Folha de S. Paulo
reported today.  Renault , with Japanese affiliate Nissan Motor Co., plans to
boost market share to 10 percent from 5.6 percent, the newspaper
said, citing  Jean-Michel Jalinier , president of the French
automakerâ€™s local unit.  The company plans to invest 1 billion reais ($591.8
million) in Brazil, the newspaper said. Renault, based in
Boulogne-Billancourt, France, also plans to debut three new
models there, according to the report.  To contact the reporters on this story:
